fields.Title: APT / EMPTY ROOM DOOR
fields.Description: APARTMENT #10. A door leading to the apt with a real estate agent.

fields.Title: Suggestion: "There's no sweet-talking your way i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There's no sweet-talking your way in there. Be official.

fields.Title: Half Light: "Scare them. Suspected of some *big..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Scare them. Suspected of some *big crime*!

fields.Title: Locked Door: "The walking stops abruptly, but no..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The walking stops abruptly, but no one comes to the door.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "You can feel tension on the other s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You can feel tension on the other side.

fields.Title: Locked Door: ""Oh, come on!" There's a pause, bef..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh, come on!" There's a pause, before you hear the door being unlocked.

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Let's go," the lieutenant says, "w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Let's go," the lieutenant says, "we don't have a reason to get inside that apartment."

fields.Title: You: ""I don't need a warrant if I suspec..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't need a warrant if I suspect there's been a *break-in*."

fields.Title: You: "Knock."
fields.Dialogue Text: Knock.

fields.Title: Locked Door: "You hear someone walking around ins..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You hear someone walking around inside, rearranging the furniture. The number on the panel says #10.

fields.Title: You: "Knock again."
fields.Dialogue Text: Knock again.

fields.Title: Locked Door: ""Excuse me? Of course not!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Excuse me? Of course not!"

fields.Title: Locked Door: "The door number #10 is closed again..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The door number #10 is closed again.

fields.Title: Perception (Hearing): "Sounded like a woman. A woman's sho..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Sounded like a woman. A woman's shoes.

fields.Title: Logic: "You have *plenty* of reason to ente..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You have *plenty* of reason to enter.

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Well, that was easy."
fields.Dialogue Text: Well, that was easy.

fields.Title: You: ""Are you cooking *morphine* in ther..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Are you cooking *morphine* in there?!"

fields.Title: You: "Knock."
fields.Dialogue Text: Knock.

fields.Title: Locked Door: ""Do I *have to* open the door?" You..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Do I *have to* open the door?" You hear the clacking of heels again, as the other side walks right up to the door. Her tone is now getting a defensive edge...

fields.Title: Locked Door: ""Do you have a warrant? I'm not obl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Do you have a warrant? I'm not obligated to open the door if you don't have a warrant."

fields.Title: You: ""Then open the door, so I can *veri..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Then open the door, so I can *verify* your identity."

fields.Title: Locked Door: "This time the steps come closer. "W..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This time the steps come closer. "Who is this?" demands a female voice, wary and tense.

fields.Title: You: ""This is the police. Open up.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is the police. Open up."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""That was smart," the lieutenant sa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That was smart," the lieutenant says, nodding toward the unlocked door.

fields.Title: Locked Door: "Nothing happens. The real estate ag..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Nothing happens. The real estate agent must have left.

fields.Title: Logic: "It's generally easier to do things..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's generally easier to do things if you have literally *any* reason.

fields.Title: You: ""This apartment is supposed to be e..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This apartment is supposed to be empty. Did you break in here?"

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Later then. Entering this door seem..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Later then. Entering this door seems a physical *challenge*.
